Malacoctenus erdmani is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the western Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea from the Bahamas to Cura√ßao.  This species is an inhabitant of reefs where it prefers areas that provide hiding places such as coral rubble and rock and patches of algae.  It can reach a length of 3.8 centimetres (1.5 in) TL. The specific name honours the fishery biologist Donald S. Erdman.